Sentencas: In this work, La2NiO4+delta is used as cathode material for Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction of YSZ/La2NiO4+δ using an ultrathin La2NiO4+δ interfacial layer

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy, X-ray diffraction, and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy are used to investigate the effect of the presence of an ultrathin La(2)NiO4(+delta) layer (80 nm) deposited by dip-coating or sputtering at the interface YSZ/La2NiO4+delta.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction of YSZ/La2NiO4+δ using an ultrathin La2NiO4+δ interfacial layer

Sentencas: The thick porous cathode layer of La2NiO4+delta is deposited by screen-printing, and sintered at 1000 degrees C for 2 h or 1200 degrees C for 20 min in order to study the effect of sintering temperature on the electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction of YSZ/La2NiO4+δ using an ultrathin La2NiO4+δ interfacial layer

Sentencas: The results show that the electrochemical performances of the cathode are influenced by the deposition technique.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction of YSZ/La2NiO4+δ using an ultrathin La2NiO4+δ interfacial layer

Sentencas: The best electrochemical properties are obtained with the use of the nano film interface layer deposited by sputtering.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction of YSZ/La2NiO4+δ using an ultrathin La2NiO4+δ interfacial layer

Sentencas: The introduction of ultrathin interface with nano grained between the cathode and electrolyte is a promising technique to reduce polarization resistance associated with oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) on the cathode.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction of YSZ/La2NiO4+δ using an ultrathin La2NiO4+δ interfacial layer
